This paper is likely to belong to the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category as it focuses on improving system throughput by co-locating tasks on the same host. It could also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category as it deals with data analytic applications built upon big data processing frameworks. The paper's use of machine learning techniques to model memory behavior suggests it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper's focus on improving system performance through task co-location suggests it could belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of a mixture-of-experts approach to model memory behavior suggests it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
